           SHORT="KDE 3 System Moniter."
cat << EOF
KSim (the K System Information Monitor) is a plug-in-based system monitor application. It is similar to GKrellm.  Features include:   


host name display;
uptime, memory and swap plugins;
scrolling disk information plugin;
eth0, ppp0 and other network interfaces plugin;
plugin for any sensor for lm_sensors;
CPU usage plugin;
plugin for /proc, with a graph to display load, forks, current number of processes and current number of users (planned);
APM laptop battery meter plugin (planned); and
support for GKrellm themes (almost completed).
EOF
